 Reynolds|Maximum Effort]] and [[Campbell Grobman Films]]\n|-\n|{{dts|2020|10|9}}\n| ''[[Fatale (film)|Fatale]]''\n| distribution only; produced by Hidden Empire Film Group and Endeavor Content<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/lionsgate-nabs-hilary-swanks-noir-thriller-fatale-1233880|title=Lionsgate Nabs Hilary Swank's Noir Thriller 'Fatale'|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Etan|last=Vlessing|date=August 22, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Fatale-(2019)#tab=summary|title=Fatale|website=The-Numbers|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|2021|1|22}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/chaos-walking-daisy-ridley-tom-holland-january-2021-release-1202854439/|title=\u2018Chaos Walking\u2019 Eyes January 2021 Release|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|date=February 7, 2020|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n| ''[[Chaos Walking (film)|Chaos Walking]]''\n| co-production with [[ImageMovers]] and Allison Shearmur Productions\n|-\n|{{dts|2021|5|21}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/john-wick-4-summer-2021-lionsgate-1203221620/|title=\u2018John Wick 4\u2019 Confirmed With a 2021 Release Date {{!}} Variety|last=McNary|first=Dave|website=www.variety.com|language=en|access-date=May 20, 2019}}</ref>\n| ''[[John Wick: Chapter 3 \u2013 Parabellum#Sequel|John Wick: Chapter 4]]''\n| distribution only; produced by [[Summit Entertainment]], [[Thunder Road Pictures]], and 87Eleven Productions\n|-\n| TBA\n| ''[[Antebellum (film)|Antebellum]]''\n| distribution only; produced by QC Entertainment\n|-\n|TBA<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/lionsgate-suspense-thriller-run-sets-2020-release-date-1181564|title=Lionsgate Suspense Thriller 'Run' Sets 2020 Release Date|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Etan|last=Vlessing|date=January 31, 2019|accessdate=January 31, 2019}}</ref>\n| ''[[Run (2020 film)|Run]]'